ations concerned with the economic welfare of Philadelphia and its environs, its significance is more than local. It compares trends in the nation and in other metropolitan centers with those in Philadelphia. In addition the economic development problems of cities in general and the flexibilities and inflexibilities of an urban labor force in adjusting to a changing economy receive considerable attention.The statistical data, methodology, and analysis will be of value to regional economists, labor market analysts, and students of manpower problems in major industrial and occupational groups.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aLaborzPennsylvaniazPhiladelphia. 0aWorking classzPennsylvaniazPhiladelphia. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Economic Conditions.2bisacsh  aBooks of Regional Interest.  aBusiness.  aEconomics.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Pennsylvania Press Package Archive 1898-1999z978311044252640uhttps://doi.org/10.9783/978151280511640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781512805116423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781512805116.jpg  a978-3-11-044252-6  University of Pennsylvania Press Package Archive 1898-1999c1898d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LAEC  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK